transcript.text: Hello, welcome back to the On Print Shop Designer Studio tutorial series.
In today's video we will learn to create a PDF block path in Coreldraw tool.
Creating a block PDF path in Coreldraw involves designing a shape or path that will be saved as a PDF with no stroke and a solid full color.
Here's how you can do it.
Open your file in Coreldraw.
You can use the Smart Fill tool to create a path, as it offers a straightforward and efficient approach.
Other tools, such as the pen tool or Bezier tool, can also be used for path creation, depending on your design requirements.
Choose the most suitable tool for your project.
Now, set the Fill color property to None.
Copy the path and paste it into a new document.
Next, adjust the resolution to 72 DPI and then click OK.
Resize the page to fit the shape you've designed.
Set the pages height and width according to the path size.
Click OK Position the path at the center of the document.
You can use the shortcut P to center the path on the page.
Select the path and export it in SVG format.
Click Export.
You need to make sure that you check the export settings for the path.
Your path is saved on the desktop.
Open the document using Notepad++.
Select the path.
Copy this path to paste it into the Custom Properties window.
In the PDF Block plugin, open your PDF file with Adobe Acrobat.
Access the PDF Lib Blocks menu to activate the PDF Lib Block tool.
Create a single block using the PDF Lib Block plugin.

When drawing the block, consider the following #1 the block should cover the top left corner of the path #2 blocks should cover the top right corner of the path #3 blocks should cover the bottom part of the path.
Number four blocks should cover the top part of the path.
Ensure the right, left, bottom, and top sides of the blocks align perfectly with the paths borders.
Select the type of block.
In this case it's the image block.
Set block properties using the property window.
Specify the fit method and position.
Add the default image as needed.
Additionally, you can include custom properties.
Your PDF file is now prepared for uploading.
Save the file from the File menu.
Add a clip path to the image block using Manage Properties and you have successfully created the block PDF path in the Corel Draw tool.
We hope these instructions provided a clear and organized workflow for creating and processing your Corel Draw design.
Hope you enjoyed the video.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on onprintshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
